President Donald J. Trump has signed a proclamation declaring January 16 as National Religious Freedom Day in the United States. The day commemorates the anniversary of the passage of the 1786 Virginia Statute for Religious Freedom, which outlined the principles of true respect for freedom of religion. The proclamation emphasizes the importance of religious freedom in America and around the world, and the commitment of the Trump Administration to protect and support it. The proclamation states that religious freedom is a source of personal and national stability, and that faith brings life and hope to the world.